5|$|In late 1958, <b>Ernest</b> <b>Hemingway</b> {{acquired}} {{the rights to}} produce a film version of Burnham's memoirs, Scouting on Two Continents. CBS immediately contracted Hemingway to produce the film for television, with Gary Cooper expressing considerable interest in playing the part of Burnham. Hemingway was already behind schedule with other commitments, however, and no work had been done on the movie when he committed suicide in July 1961.|$|E
